Mr Rees-Mogg was appointed as the Minister for Brexit Opportunities earlier this month with a task to examine how Britain can benefit from leaving the European Union. Imperial measurements fell out of business use when Britain joined the European common market in the early 1970s and Mr Rees-Mogg is now on track to revive the old British way of labelling. Conservative business minister Paul Scully said reintroducing imperial labelling would be “an important step in taking back control” and that a planned “assessment of the economic impact on business will be carried out in due course”. FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES... 